-- Romanian Nine-Month Energy Output Declines on Crude Oil, Gas; Imports Fall
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2010-11-05T08:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/romanian-nine-month-energy-output-declines-on-crude-oil-gas-imports-fall.html
Romanian energy production dropped
0.5 percent in the first nine months because of a decline in
crude production.  Energy generation declined to 17.1 million metric tons of
oil equivalent, the  National Statistics Institute  said today in
an e-mailed statement. Energy imports dropped 0.2 percent to 8.2
million tons, according to the Bucharest-based institute.  Crude oil output shrank 2.7 percent to about 3 million tons
of oil equivalent and the natural-gas production fell 2.8
percent to 6.3 million tons, the institute said. Coal production
declined 0.3 percent to 4.4 million tons of oil equivalent,
according to the institute.  Electricity use advanced 4.2 percent to 37.5 billion
kilowatt-hours as domestic consumption rose 2.4 percent, while
public lighting use decreased 3.2 percent, the institute said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andra Timu  in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  